Essential Terraform Commands for DevOps Engineers: A Quick Reference Guide🎯
 
🔸terraform init - Initializes the working directory and downloads provider plugins.
🔸terraform plan - Previews infrastructure changes without applying them.
🔸terraform validate - Checks the configuration files for syntax errors.
🔸terraform fmt - Formats configuration files for consistency.
🔸terraform apply - Provisions or updates infrastructure interactively.
🔸terraform apply -auto-approve - Applies changes without confirmation.
🔸terraform show - Displays the current state or execution plan.
🔸terraform state list - Lists all resources in the state file.
🔸terraform state show <resource> - Shows details of a specific resource in the state.
🔸terraform state mv <source> <destination> - Moves resources within the state file.
🔸terraform state rm <resource> - Removes a resource from the state file.
🔸terraform destroy - Deletes all resources managed by terraform.
🔸terraform destroy -target=<resource> - Deletes a specific resource.
🔸terraform providers - Lists all providers and their versions.
🔸terraform import <resource> <id> - Imports existing resources into terraform.
🔸terraform refresh - Updates the state file with the latest resource info.
🔸TF_LOG=DEBUG terraform apply - Enables debugging logs for troubleshooting.
🔸terraform console - Opens an interactive console for expressions.
🔸terraform get - Downloads or updates modules used in configurations.
🔸terraform workspace list - Lists all available workspaces.
🔸terraform workspace new <name> - Creates a new workspace.
🔸terraform workspace select <name> - Switches to a different workspace.
🔸terraform workspace delete <name> - Deletes an existing workspace.
🔸terraform lock - Creates or updates the dependency lock file.
🔸terraform output - Displays values defined in the outputs section.
🔸terraform output -json - Exports outputs in JSON format.
🔸terraform plan -out=tfplan - Saves the execution plan to a file.
🔸terraform apply tfplan - Applies the saved execution plan.
🔸terraform fmt -recursive - Formats all .tf files recursively.
🔸terraform apply -input=false - Runs apply non-interactively for automation
